In Spanish poetry , the syntactic configurations under which enjambment takes place have been described extensively , and detailed studies on the use of enjambment by individual authors exist ( see Martínez Cantón , 2011 for an overview ) including , among others Quilis ( 1964 ) , Domínguez Caparrós , ( 2000 ) , Paraíso , ( 2000 ) , Spang ( 1983 ) for a description of enjambment , and Alarcos ( 1966 ) , Senabre ( 1982 ) , Luján ( 2006 ) , Martínez Fernández ( 2010 ) for case - studies on a single author . ||| ADP ADJ NOUN PUNCT DET ADJ NOUN ADP PRON NOUN VERB NOUN AUX AUX VERB ADV PUNCT In Spanish tradition , enjambment ( in Spanish , " encabalgamiento " ) is considered to take place when a pause suggested by poetic form ( e.g. at the end of a line or across hemistichs ) occurs between strongly connected lexical or syntactic units , triggering an unnatural cut between those units . ||| ADP ADJ NOUN PUNCT NOUN PUNCT ADP PROPN PUNCT PUNCT X PUNCT PUNCT AUX VERB PART VERB NOUN ADV DET NOUN VERB ADP ADJ NOUN PUNCT ADV ADP DET NOUN ADP DET NOUN CCONJ ADP NOUN PUNCT VERB ADP ADV VERB ADJ CCONJ ADJ NOUN PUNCT VERB DET ADJ NOUN ADP DET NOUN PUNCT ||| SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_amod REDUCE_L_case SHIFT REDUCE_R_punct SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_case SHIFT REDUCE_R_punct SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_punct REDUCE_L_nmod REDUCE_L_punct SHIFT REDUCE_R_punct SHIFT REDUCE_R_punct REDUCE_R_appos SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_aux REDUCE_L_nsubj REDUCE_L_obl SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_mark SHIFT REDUCE_R_obj REDUCE_R_xcomp SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_det SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_amod REDUCE_L_case REDUCE_R_obl REDUCE_R_acl SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_det REDUCE_L_case REDUCE_L_advmod REDUCE_L_punct SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_det REDUCE_L_case REDUCE_R_nmod SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_case REDUCE_L_cc REDUCE_R_conj SHIFT REDUCE_R_punct REDUCE_R_nmod SHIFT REDUCE_L_nsubj REDUCE_L_advmod SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_advmod SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_cc REDUCE_R_conj SHIFT REDUCE_L_amod REDUCE_L_amod REDUCE_L_case REDUCE_R_obl SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_punct SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_amod REDUCE_L_det SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_det REDUCE_L_case REDUCE_R_nmod REDUCE_R_obj REDUCE_R_advcl REDUCE_R_advcl SHIFT REDUCE_R_punct

Pierre Charles L'Enfant ( French : [ pjɛʁ ʃɑʁl lɑ̃fɑ̃ ] ; August 2 , 1754 – June 14 , 1825 ) , self - identified as Peter Charles L'Enfant while living in the United States , was a French - born American military engineer who designed the basic plan for Washington , D.C. L'Enfant was born in Paris , France on August 2 , 1754 , the third child and second son of Pierre L'Enfant ( 1704 – 1787 ) , a painter with a good reputation in the service of King Louis XV of France , ( 1710 - 1774 , reigned 1715 - 1774 ) , and Marie L'Enfant , the daughter of a minor official at court . ||| PROPN AUX VERB ADP PROPN PUNCT PROPN ADP PROPN NUM PUNCT NUM PUNCT DET ADJ NOUN CCONJ ADJ NOUN ADP PROPN PROPN PUNCT NUM SYM NUM PUNCT PUNCT DET NOUN ADP DET ADJ NOUN ADP DET NOUN ADP PROPN PROPN NUM ADP PROPN PUNCT PUNCT NUM SYM NUM PUNCT VERB NUM SYM NUM PUNCT PUNCT CCONJ PROPN PROPN PUNCT DET NOUN ADP DET ADJ NOUN ADP NOUN PUNCT ||| SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_aux REDUCE_L_nsubj SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_case SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_punct REDUCE_R_appos REDUCE_R_obl SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_compound REDUCE_L_case SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_punct REDUCE_R_nmod REDUCE_R_obl SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_amod REDUCE_L_det REDUCE_L_punct SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_amod REDUCE_L_cc REDUCE_R_conj SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_case SHIFT REDUCE_R_flat SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_punct SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_case REDUCE_R_nmod SHIFT REDUCE_R_punct REDUCE_R_nmod SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_det REDUCE_L_punct SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_amod REDUCE_L_det REDUCE_L_case SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_det REDUCE_L_case SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_case SHIFT REDUCE_R_flat SHIFT REDUCE_R_dep SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_case REDUCE_R_nmod SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_punct REDUCE_L_punct SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_case REDUCE_R_nmod REDUCE_R_nmod SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_punct SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_case REDUCE_R_nmod REDUCE_R_obl SHIFT REDUCE_R_punct REDUCE_R_parataxis REDUCE_R_nmod REDUCE_R_nmod REDUCE_R_nmod REDUCE_R_appos SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_cc REDUCE_L_punct SHIFT REDUCE_R_flat SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_det REDUCE_L_punct SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_amod REDUCE_L_det REDUCE_L_case SHIFT SHIFT REDUCE_L_case REDUCE_R_nmod REDUCE_R_nmod REDUCE_R_appos REDUCE_R_conj REDUCE_R_nmod REDUCE_R_advcl SHIFT REDUCE_R_punct

Moreau was born in Paris , the daughter of Katherine ( née Buckley ) , a dancer who performed at the Folies Bergère ( d. 1990 ) , and Anatole - Désiré Moreau , a restaurateur ( d. 1975 ) . After 1949 , she began appearing in films with small parts but continued primarily active in the theatre for several years — a year at the Théâtre National Populaire opposite among others Gérard Philipe and Robert Hirsch , then a breakout two years in dual roles in The Dazzling Hour by Anna Bonacci , then Jean Cocteau 's La Machine Infernale and others before another two - year run , this time in Shaw 's Pygmalion . Eugene A.
